parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: No brakes or reduced braking power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
puddle of brake fluid under the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose control or fail to stop effectively, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: vehicle rolls a couple of yards before stopping
grinding noise when applying ABS brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Rotor Warping and Premature Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped or prematurely worn brake rotors can cause vibration, noise, and reduced braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: premature wear of front brake pads
rotors turned multiple times due to grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate oil pressure gauge can lead to engine damage or failure if the driver is not aware of low oil pressure.
symptoms: Oil pressure gauge reads excessively high
"Check Oil" and "Check Gauges" warning lights flash sporadically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to not start, stall while driving, or even catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A faulty alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the electrical system can cause fuses to blow, leading to loss of tail lights and flashers, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: loss of tail lights and flashers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause damage to property and potentially harm occupants.
A cracked engine head can cause coolant loss, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Engine bearing failure can cause the engine to seize or lock up, leading to sudden loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
Water pump failure can cause coolant loss, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Intake manifold gasket failure can cause coolant loss, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Radiator core failure can cause coolant loss, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Map sensor failure can cause erratic engine operation, poor performance, and potentially lead to engine damage.
